EDA of Loan Data by Amanullah Ashraf

This data set is about the people bought loan. How much is their loan, their credit grade, occupation, income range, loan amout, stated monthly income, employment status etc.

Univariate Analysis

What is the structure of your dataset?

Loan data set is compsed of 113937 obersvation and 81 variables. In the data set there

are values which are numceric and other are categorical. It contain information about

peolple who took loan and their current ststus. It contain information about their occupation

thier income, state, credit rating, loan status, employment staus etc.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?

Borrower Occupation, thier income range and how much loan original amount they got and how

many have paid them back.

What other features in the dataset do you think will help support your
investigation into your feature(s) of interest?

Other columns like borrower credit rating, borrower state, stated monthly income etc are

helpful as well in investigation.

Did you create any new variables from existing variables in the dataset?

No new variable is created as data set already contain quite large number of variables.

Of the features you investigated, were there any unusual distributions?
Did you perform any operations on the data to tidy, adjust, or change the form
of the data? If so, why did you do this?

Colums which I am using is quite clean. I didnt feel any need to clean it.

Final Plots and Summary

Plot One

Description One

Borrower of different income range are shown on the X-axis and their corresponding loan amount are on the Y-axis. From the above graph we can say that there is a kind of symetry of the loan amount taken. Except $100,000+ income range group, almost all other group took, $25000 loan amount. The highest loan amount taken by $100,000 income range group i.e $35,000. They are good traget market segmentation for the lender. Lender can offer them different products inorder to retain them.

Plot Two

Description Two

From the above graph we can say that most of the loan are taken by those whose monthly income is from $0 to $25,000. This group almost took $35,000 loan amount. The second major chunck on X-axis is from From 25,000 to 50,000. Except few exceptions, the second group on average took $25000 loan amount. One major thing to note from the above graph is, those whose monthly income ranging from $0 to $25000 took most of the loan. One reson might be that they have low monthly income, so inorder to meet their expenses they need to take loan. Lender can target this group in their markting stratigies.

Description Three

From the above graph we can see that loan amounts were given to both Employed and Retired persons. We can see that loan amount to Retired people were $10000 majority of the times, but people were given in $10,000 to $25000 range as well. employed people are all over the placeses on the graph. This shows that employed people are availaing more loan than retired people. Lender can come up with some good product for employed segment of loan borrower.

Reflection

From the graphs drwan above we can observe the following information: According to loan status, majority of the people fall under “Currently” section, means currently majority of people have taken loan who are employed under the income range of $25000 to $49,999. Majority of the people took upto $25000 loan amount. State wise, people from California took most of the loan. Almost half of the population of the borrower are home owners. Occupation wise highest among them who took loan is Nurse(RN). So we can hypothesise by saying that, currently people are under debt, mostly from california who are employed under the Nurse(RN) occupation with the monthly income range of $25000 > to $49,999. We can further test our hypothesis by doing regression analysis.

Plot 1 shows income range of the people and their borrwed amount. One of the income range group took $35000 loan. They are good traget market for lender. Lender can introduce new products to them, offer discount, offer prizes etc.
From the above plot 2 we can say that most of the loan are taken by those whose monthly income is from $0 to $25,000. Low imcome are majority who avail the loan opportunity. Plot 3 shows that Employed people are availaing more loan than retired people. Why is that? Are they unable to meet their expenses from their job as they are employed or inflation is high which in turn forced them to take loan? From so many columns it is difficiult to a select few colums for analysis. Good thing about Data set is, it is almost clean, while analyzing. It is a surprises to know that people who are retired also got loan amount.
